# A concise description of what this element means (e.g. for use in autogenerated summaries).
#: StructureDefinition.element.Patient.identifier:passportLocal/short
msgid "Local passport / ID card number"
msgstr "Номер местного паспорта / ID-карты"

# Provides a complete explanation of the meaning of the data element for human readability.  For the case of elements derived from existing elements (e.g. constraints), the definition SHALL be consistent with the base definition, but convey the meaning of the element in the particular context of use of the resource. (Note: The text you are reading is specified in ElementDefinition.definition).
#: StructureDefinition.element.Patient.identifier:passportLocal/definition
msgid "Local (internal) passport number, shared by the modern ID card and the older book-form passport. Set use = official for the credential currently in force (typically the ID card) and use = old for a superseded paper passport number."
msgstr "Номер местного (внутреннего) паспорта, общий для современной ID-карты и более старого паспорта в виде книжки. Указывайте use = official для действующего документа (обычно ID-карта) и use = old для устаревшего бумажного паспорта."

# A concise description of what this element means (e.g. for use in autogenerated summaries).
#: StructureDefinition.element.Patient.identifier:passportForeign/short
msgid "Foreign passport number"
msgstr "Foreign passport number"

# Provides a complete explanation of the meaning of the data element for human readability.  For the case of elements derived from existing elements (e.g. constraints), the definition SHALL be consistent with the base definition, but convey the meaning of the element in the particular context of use of the resource. (Note: The text you are reading is specified in ElementDefinition.definition).
#: StructureDefinition.element.Patient.identifier:passportForeign/definition
msgid "Passport identifier for foreign nationals. System URI pattern: https://dhp.uz/fhir/core/sid/pid/{country-code}/ppn where {country-code} is the ISO 3166-1 two-letter country code (e.g., 'ee' for Estonia, 'ru' for Russia)."
msgstr "Passport identifier for foreign nationals. System URI pattern: https://dhp.uz/fhir/core/sid/pid/{country-code}/ppn where {country-code} is the ISO 3166-1 two-letter country code (e.g., 'ee' for Estonia, 'ru' for Russia)."

# A concise description of what this element means (e.g. for use in autogenerated summaries).
#: StructureDefinition.element.Patient.identifier:pensionNumber/short
msgid "Used to identify a patient's pension status and pension type."
msgstr "Used to identify a patient's pension status and pension type."

# Provides a complete explanation of the meaning of the data element for human readability.  For the case of elements derived from existing elements (e.g. constraints), the definition SHALL be consistent with the base definition, but convey the meaning of the element in the particular context of use of the resource. (Note: The text you are reading is specified in ElementDefinition.definition).
#: StructureDefinition.element.Patient.identifier:pensionNumber/definition
msgid "Naming system defining the pension number identifier issued by the Ministry of Finance of the Republic of Uzbekistan (Pension Fund), as referenced by the national identifier system and integrated with the e-government platform (iskm.egov.uz/minfin/services/pension/pinnp). The pension number associated with different pension types, including old-age pension, disability pension, survivor's pension, and other pension categories."
msgstr "Naming system defining the pension number identifier issued by the Ministry of Finance of the Republic of Uzbekistan (Pension Fund), as referenced by the national identifier system and integrated with the e-government platform (iskm.egov.uz/minfin/services/pension/pinnp). The pension number associated with different pension types, including old-age pension, disability pension, survivor's pension, and other pension categories."

